report line**\\\\n\\\\nI’m wondering if the dynamic report line isn't actually `Class.forName(\\\\\\\"javax.servlet.jsp.tagext.JspTag\\\\\\\")` when using `findAncestor`. It seems that might just be a helper function rather than the main class I'm expecting. It’s a bit confusing to figure out what each part is really doing. I’ll need to dig deeper to clarify this and ensure I’m on the right path!\\\"},{\\\"type\\\":\\\"summary_text\\\",\\\"text\\\":\\\"**Considering metadata collection**\\\\n\\\\nI’m pondering whether the metadata collection only applies to the test method. It feels uncertain because static initialization might not be included during the discovery phase. That doesn’t seem ideal. Should I consider creating a field initializer for the test? Hmm, that might not work either, especially if the previous test file isn’t getting tracked and therefore isn't within the workflow. It's definitely something I need to clarify.\\\"},{\\\"type\\\":\\\"summary_text\\\",\\\"text\\\":\\\"**Evaluating file outputs and structure**\\\\n\\\\nI noticed that `git diff` showed no output for the new file since it was untracked, but external tools can still see it. I’m wondering if the workflow tests just the current worktree and not untracked files. Perhaps the test fails due to the public visibility requirement for top-level test classes. I might need to refine the structure to use nested classes instead. Also, it seems I should avoid using `$` in file/class names to prevent complications with naming conventions.\\\"},{\\\"type\\\":\\\"summary_text\\\",\\\"text\\\":\\\"**Examining test class structure**\\\\n\\\\nI see there's no issue with \\\\\\\"all top-level test classes public,\\\\\\\" but there’s a one-to-one mapping between report classes and generated test files. Top-level helpers in the same file could count as extra classes, so I might need to reconsider that. Using static nested classes seems disallowed because of the `$` in bytecode names. Instead, I could focus on using built-in classes like SimpleTagSupport and JspTag without adding helpers. I need to cover the TagAdapter.getAdaptee branch in the active class, possibly setting TagSupport as a parent class to reason through the structure.\\\"},{\\\"type\\\":\\\"summary_text\\\",\\\"text\\\":\\\"**Reviewing TagAdapter implementation**\\\\n\\\\nI see that the TagAdapter constructor needs a SimpleTag. I can create an instance of SimpleTagSupport with `adaptedParent = new SimpleTagSupport();` and then set the parent in the child with `child.setParent(new TagAdapter(adaptedParent));`. This lets me find `adaptedParent`, which is great.\\\\n\\\\nHowever, I'm a bit concerned that if the `class$` isn't covered, this might not completely resolve the issue. That's something I need to keep in mind as I work on this.\\\"}]}\"}, {\"type\": \"toolCall\", \"id\": \"call_DGnaznxjQNurmIn68iDqGNNl|fc_0cffb71c604539cd0169f51b388b80819ca534bd102682855c\", \"name\": \"edit\", \"arguments\": {\"path\": \"tests/src/jspapi/jsp-api/2.0-20040521/src/test/java/jspapi/jsp_api/SimpleTagSupportTest.java\", \"edits\": [{\"oldText\": \"import javax.servlet.jsp.tagext.JspTag;\\nimport javax.servlet.jsp.tagext.SimpleTagSupport;\\n\", \"newText\": \"import javax.servlet.jsp.tagext.JspTag;\\nimport javax.servlet.jsp.tagext.SimpleTagSupport;\\nimport javax.servlet.jsp.tagext.TagAdapter;\\n\"}, {\"oldText\": \"public class SimpleTagSupportTest {\\n    @Test\\n    void findsNearestAncestorUsingSimpleTagParentChain() {\\n        MarkedSimpleTagSupport grandparent = new MarkedSimpleTagSupport();\\n        SimpleTagSupport parent = new SimpleTagSupport();\\n        SimpleTagSupport child = new SimpleTagSupport();\\n        parent.setParent(grandparent);\\n        child.setParent(parent);\\n\\n        Class<?> parentType = parent.getClass();\\n        JspTag directAncestor = SimpleTagSupport.findAncestorWithClass(child, parentType);\\n        JspTag markedAncestor = SimpleTagSupport.findAncestorWithClass(child, SimpleTagSupportMarker.class);\\n        JspTag unsupportedAncestor = SimpleTagSupport.findAncestorWithClass(child, Object.class);\\n\\n        assertThat(directAncestor).isSameAs(parent);\\n        assertThat(markedAncestor).isSameAs(grandparent);\\n        assertThat(unsupportedAncestor).isNull();\\n    }\\n}\\n\\ninterface SimpleTagSupportMarker {\\n}\\n\\nclass MarkedSimpleTagSupport extends SimpleTagSupport implements SimpleTagSupportMarker {\\n}\\n\", \"newText\": \"public class SimpleTagSupportTest {\\n    @Test\\n    void findsNearestAncestorUsingSimpleTagParentChain() {\\n        SimpleTagSupport grandparent = new SimpleTagSupport();\\n        SimpleTagSupport parent = new SimpleTagSupport();\\n        SimpleTagSupport child = new SimpleTagSupport();\\n        parent.setParent(grandparent);\\n        child.setParent(parent);\\n\\n        JspTag nearestJspTagAncestor = SimpleTagSupport.findAncestorWithClass(child, JspTag.class);\\n        JspTag nearestSimpleTagAncestor = SimpleTagSupport.findAncestorWithClass(child, parent.getClass());\\n        JspTag unsupportedAncestor = SimpleTagSupport.findAncestorWithClass(child, Object.class);\\n\\n        assertThat(nearestJspTagAncestor).isSameAs(parent);\\n        assertThat(nearestSimpleTagAncestor).isSameAs(parent);\\n        assertThat(unsupportedAncestor).isNull();\\n    }\\n\\n    @Test\\n    void unwrapsTagAdapterAncestorBeforeMatching() {\\n        SimpleTagSupport adaptedParent = new SimpleTagSupport();\\n        SimpleTagSupport child = new SimpleTagSupport();\\n        child.setParent(new TagAdapter(adaptedParent));\\n\\n        JspTag ancestor = SimpleTagSupport.findAncestorWithClass(child, SimpleTagSupport.class);\\n\\n        assertThat(ancestor).isSameAs(adaptedParent);\\n    }\\n}\\n\"}]}}], \"api\": \"openai-responses\", \"provider\": \"OCA\", \"model\": \"gpt-5.5\", \"usage\": {\"input\": 21094, \"output\": 2368, \"cacheRead\": 0, \"cacheWrite\": 0, \"totalTokens\": 23462, \"cost\": {\"input\": 0, \"ou